---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Allianz Care in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'Spanish Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'spain-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Spanish Insurers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-in-spain', text: 'Using Your Insurance in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Allianz in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'spainPrice', header: 'Spain (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Essential', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', spainPrice: '$80-110/mo', visaCompliant: 'Check requirements' },
  { plan: 'Classic', coverage: 'Essential + Outpatient', spainPrice: '$120-160/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'Premium', coverage: 'Comprehensive', spainPrice: '$160-220/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Premium + Enhanced', spainPrice: '$200-280/mo', visaCompliant: true },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'allianz', header: 'Allianz Care' },
  { key: 'spanish', header: 'Spanish Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', allianz: '$120-160', spanish: '$60-120' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside Spain', allianz: 'Worldwide', spanish: 'Limited/None' },
  { factor: 'Network in Spain', allianz: 'Very extensive', spanish: 'Very extensive' },
  { factor: 'English Support', allianz: '24/7 multilingual', spanish: 'Varies' },
  { factor: 'Deductible Savings', allianz: 'Up to 60% off', spanish: 'Limited options' },
  { factor: 'Portability if You Move', allianz: 'Fully portable', spanish: 'Must cancel' },
  { factor: 'Mental Health', allianz: 'Good coverage', spanish: 'Often limited' },
  { factor: 'Visa Acceptance', allianz: 'Widely accepted', spanish: 'Accepted' },
];

const hospitalColumns = [
  { key: 'city', header: 'City' },
  { key: 'hospitals', header: 'Major Network Hospitals' },
  { key: 'directBilling', header: 'Direct Billing' },
];

const hospitalRows = [
  { city: 'Madrid', hospitals: 'Hospital Ruber Internacional, Clínica Universidad de Navarra, Sanitas La Moraleja', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Barcelona', hospitals: 'Hospital Quirónsalud Barcelona, Centro Médico Teknon, Hospital Plató', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Valencia', hospitals: 'Hospital Quirónsalud Valencia, Hospital 9 de Octubre', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Málaga', hospitals: 'Hospital Quirónsalud Málaga, Hospiten Estepona', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Seville', hospitals: 'Hospital Quirónsalud Infanta Luisa, Hospital Viamed Santa Ángela de la Cruz', directBilling: true },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care Health Insurance in Spain"
  description="Complete guide to using Allianz Care in Spain. Visa compliance, local network, pricing, and how it compares to Spanish insurers."
  headline="Allianz Care Health Insurance in Spain"
  subheadline="Is Allianz Care the right choice for expats in Spain? Coverage, costs, and how their European roots benefit Spain-based expats."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/spain-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Allianz Spain Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Allianz Care in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care is a strong choice for expats in Spain, particularly those who want European-based insurance with extensive flexibility. As a German company with deep European roots, Allianz has one of the strongest networks in Spain and across the EU.
  </p>
  <p>
    The standout feature for Spain: Allianz offers high-deductible options that can reduce premiums by up to 60%. Given that routine healthcare in Spain is affordable, this strategy lets you save significantly while maintaining strong coverage for major expenses.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">2M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers worldwide</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">60%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Max deductible savings</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">4</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Plan tiers available</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Spain-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Allianz Care costs for expats living in Spain."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">Spanish Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care plans are accepted for Spanish visa applications, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Non-Lucrative Visa</strong> (retirement visa)</li>
    <li><strong>Digital Nomad Visa</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Student Visa</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Golden Visa</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Meeting Visa Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    For Spanish visas, particularly the Non-Lucrative Visa:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Choose Classic, Premium, or Platinum for outpatient coverage</li>
    <li>Request a zero-copay configuration if required by your consulate</li>
    <li>Ensure coverage starts before your visa appointment</li>
    <li>Request visa documentation in Spanish from Allianz</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">European Advantage</h3>
    <p class="text-green-800">
      As an EU-based insurer, Allianz Care is familiar with Spanish visa requirements and routinely provides compliant documentation. Their European headquarters can be an advantage when dealing with Spanish authorities who may prefer EU-regulated insurers.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="spain-network">Network Coverage in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care has one of the most extensive networks in Spain among international insurers, with strong presence in all major cities and tourist areas.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={hospitalColumns} rows={hospitalRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Network Strengths</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Major cities:</strong> Excellent coverage comparable to local insurers</li>
    <li><strong>Costa del Sol:</strong> Strong network for the large expat community</li>
    <li><strong>European travel:</strong> Seamless coverage across EU countries</li>
    <li><strong>Balearic Islands:</strong> Good coverage in Mallorca, Ibiza, Menorca</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Allianz's European focus means particularly strong coverage if you travel between Spain and other EU countries — no separate travel insurance needed.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers four plan tiers with significant price variation based on deductible choice:
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices for worldwide coverage excluding USA, €500 deductible. Prices drop significantly with higher deductibles.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>The High-Deductible Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz's deductible options go up to €5,000, which can cut premiums by 50-60%. In Spain, this makes sense because:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Private doctor visits: €50-100</li>
    <li>Basic blood tests: €30-60</li>
    <li>Specialist consultation: €80-150</li>
    <li>Urgent care visit: €100-200</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    With affordable local care, you can pay routine expenses out of pocket and save €100+/month on premiums. Your insurance then covers what matters: hospitalization, surgery, major illness.
  </p>

  <h3>Which Plan for Spain?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential:</strong> Hospital and emergency only. Pair with high deductible for lowest cost.</li>
    <li><strong>Classic:</strong> Adds outpatient. Good balance for most expats. Visa-compliant.</li>
    <li><strong>Premium:</strong> Enhanced benefits including better mental health coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Platinum:</strong> Maximum coverage. Best for families or complex health needs.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Calculate Your Savings"
    description="See how different deductible options affect your premium."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Spanish Insurers</h2>
  <p>
    How does Allianz Care compare to Spanish companies like Sanitas or ASSSA?
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Choose Allianz Care If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You travel frequently within Europe</li>
    <li>You want high-deductible premium savings</li>
    <li>You might relocate to another country</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage is important</li>
    <li>You prefer an EU-regulated insurer</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Choose a Spanish Insurer If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're committed to staying in Spain long-term</li>
    <li>Lowest possible premium is the priority</li>
    <li>You don't travel outside Spain</li>
    <li>You want the most extensive local network</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    <a href="/countries/spain/insurance">See all Spain insurance options →</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="claims-in-spain">Using Your Insurance in Spain</h2>

  <h3>Direct Billing</h3>
  <p>
    At network hospitals and clinics, show your Allianz card for cashless treatment. Allianz's strong Spanish network means direct billing is widely available in major cities.
  </p>

  <h3>Reimbursement</h3>
  <p>
    For non-network providers:
  </p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
    <li>Pay the provider (keep itemized factura)</li>
    <li>Submit via MyHealth app or online portal</li>
    <li>Typical processing: 5 business days</li>
    <li>Reimbursement to your bank account</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>MyHealth App</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz's MyHealth app lets you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Find nearby network providers</li>
    <li>Submit claims with photo upload</li>
    <li>Access digital insurance card</li>
    <li>Track claim status</li>
    <li>Contact support directly</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Language Support</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz offers multilingual support including English and Spanish. Claims documentation in Spanish is accepted without translation.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Allianz in Spain</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Expats who travel within Europe</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious (high-deductible strategy)</li>
        <li>Those who prefer EU-based insurers</li>
        <li>People who value flexibility</li>
        <li>Digital nomads in Spain</li>
        <li>Those needing mental health coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Those wanting lowest absolute premium</li>
        <li>Expats who never leave Spain</li>
        <li>Those preferring US-based insurers</li>
        <li>People needing extensive US coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Allianz Care the same as Allianz Spain?</h3>
  <p>
    No. Allianz Care is the international health insurance division, separate from Allianz Seguros (the Spanish domestic insurer). Allianz Care provides global coverage; Allianz Spain provides local Spanish coverage only.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use my Allianz Care policy if I return to Germany/EU?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. Your coverage is portable across all countries. If you relocate from Spain to another EU country, simply update your residence. No new policy or underwriting required.
  </p>

  <h3>How does the high-deductible option work?</h3>
  <p>
    You choose a deductible (€500-5,000) when purchasing. You pay healthcare costs up to that amount each year. After reaching your deductible, Allianz covers the rest. Higher deductible = lower premium.
  </p>

  <h3>Does Allianz cover dental in Spain?</h3>
  <p>
    Dental is an optional add-on, not included in base plans. Given that dental care is affordable in Spain (cleaning €40-60, filling €50-80), many expats skip dental coverage and pay out of pocket.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I need care in a small Spanish town?</h3>
  <p>
    You can see any licensed provider anywhere in Spain. In smaller towns without network providers, pay out of pocket and submit for reimbursement. For serious issues, Allianz can arrange transfer to a network hospital.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Get Covered in Spain?"
    description="Get a personalized Allianz Care quote for your situation in Spain."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Network availability, pricing, and visa requirements change. We are not insurance brokers or immigration consultants. Verify all information with Allianz Care and Spanish authorities before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
